HOUSE BILL 1379
R4 6lr2639
By: Delegate R. Long
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Vehicle Laws – Vehicle Registration Fees – Sixth Legislative District
3 FOR the purpose of reducing vehicle registration fees for certain motor vehicles owned by
4 a resident of and registered to an address in the Sixth Legislative District until a
5 replacement bridge for the collapsed Francis Scott Key Bridge opens to general
6 vehicular traffic; and generally relating to vehicle registration fees in the Sixth
7 Legislative District.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Transportation
10 Section 13–912 and 13–915 through 13–917
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Transportation
16 13–912.
17 (a) When registered with the Administration, every passenger car and station
18 wagon, except as otherwise provided in this part, is a Class A (passenger) vehicle.
19 (b) [For] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, FOR
20 each Class A (passenger) vehicle, the annual registration fee is:
21 (1) For a vehicle with a manufacturer’s shipping weight of 3,500 pounds or
22 less:
