1 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $70.50; and
2 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $80.50;
3 (2) For a vehicle with a manufacturer’s shipping weight of more than 3,500
4 pounds but not more than 3,700 pounds:
5 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $80.50; and
6 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $85.50; and
7 (3) For a vehicle with a manufacturer’s shipping weight of more than 3,700
8 pounds:
9 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $121.50; and
10 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $151.50.
11 (C) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A CLASS A (PASSENGER) VEHICLE
12 OWNED BY A RESIDENT OF AND REGISTERED TO AN ADDRESS IN THE SIXTH
13 LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT.
14 (2) FOR EACH CLASS A (PASSENGER) VEHICLE, THE ANNUAL
15 REGISTRATION FEE IS:
16 (I) FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MANUFACTURER’S SHIPPING
17 WEIGHT OF 3,500 POUNDS OR LESS, $30.50;
18 (II) FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MANUFACTURER’S SHIPPING
19 WEIGHT OF MORE THAN 3,500 POUNDS BUT NOT MORE THAN 3,700 POUNDS, $35.50;
20 AND
21 (III) FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MANUFACTURER’S SHIPPING
22 WEIGHT OF MORE THAN 3,700 POUNDS, $101.50.
23 13–915.
24 (a) When registered with the Administration, every motorcycle is a Class D
25 (motorcycle) vehicle.
26 (b) [For] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, FOR
27 each Class D (motorcycle) vehicle, the annual registration fee is:
28 (1) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $55.00; and

HOUSE BILL 1379 3
1 (2) On or after July 1, 2025, $65.00.
2 (C) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A CLASS D (MOTORCYCLE)
3 VEHICLE OWNED BY A RESIDENT OF AND REGISTERED TO AN ADDRESS IN THE SIXTH
4 LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT.
5 (2) FOR EACH CLASS D (MOTORCYCLE) VEHICLE, THE ANNUAL
6 REGISTRATION FEE IS $15.00.
7 13–916.
8 (a) When registered with the Administration, every single unit truck with two or
9 more axles is a Class E (truck) vehicle.
10 (b) (1) [For] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION,
11 FOR each Class E (truck) vehicle, the annual registration fee is based on the maximum
12 gross weight of the vehicle or combination of vehicles, as follows:
13 Maximum Gross Weight Fee (per 1,000 Pounds
14 Limit (in Pounds) or Fraction Thereof)
15 10,000 (minimum) – 18,000 $9.00
16 18,001 – 26,000 11.75
17 26,001 – 40,000 12.75
18 40,001 – 60,000 14.75
19 60,001 – 80,000 (maximum) 16.00
20 (2) (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, the annual
21 registration fee under paragraph (1) of this subsection is increased by an additional $45.00.
22 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, the annual registration fee under
23 paragraph (1) of this subsection is increased by an additional $75.00.
24 (C) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A CLASS E (TRUCK) VEHICLE THAT
25 IS:
26 (I) DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION; AND
27 (II) OWNED BY A RESIDENT OF AND REGISTERED TO AN
28 ADDRESS IN THE SIXTH LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT.
29 (2) THE ANNUAL REGISTRATION FEE FOR A CLASS E (TRUCK)
30 VEHICLE IS DECREASED BY $50.
31 13–917.

4 HOUSE BILL 1379
1 (A) [Notwithstanding] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
2 SECTION, AND NOTWITHSTANDING § 13–916(b) of this subtitle, for any Class E (truck)
3 vehicle with a manufacturer’s rated capacity of 3/4 ton or less and a maximum gross vehicle
4 weight of 7,000 pounds or less, the annual registration fee is:
5 (1) For a vehicle with a maximum gross vehicle weight of 3,500 pounds or
6 less:
7 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $83.75; and
8 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $93.75;
9 (2) Except as provided in item (4) of this section, for a vehicle with a
10 maximum gross vehicle weight of more than 3,500 pounds but not more than 5,000 pounds:
11 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $93.75; and
12 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $98.75;
13 (3) Except as provided in item (4) of this section, for a vehicle with a
14 maximum gross vehicle weight of more than 5,000 pounds:
15 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $108.75; and
16 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $138.75; and
17 (4) For a vehicle, regardless of the vehicle’s maximum gross vehicle weight,
18 for which the owner certifies on the registration application that the vehicle for which the
19 application is made will be used for construction activities:
20 (i) On or after July 1, 2024, but before July 1, 2025, $83.75; and
21 (ii) On or after July 1, 2025, $93.75.
22 (B) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A CLASS E (TRUCK) VEHICLE THAT
23 IS:
24 (I) DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION; AND
25 (II) OWNED BY A RESIDENT OF AND REGISTERED TO AN
26 ADDRESS IN THE SIXTH LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT.
27 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING § 13–916(B) OF THIS SUBTITLE, FOR ANY
28 CLASS E (TRUCK) VEHICLE WITH A MANUFACTURER’S RATED CAPACITY OF 3/4 TON
29 OR LESS AND A MAXIMUM GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT OF 7,000 POUNDS OR LESS, THE
30 ANNUAL REGISTRATION FEE IS:

HOUSE BILL 1379 5
1 (I) FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MAXIMUM GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT
2 OF 3,500 POUNDS OR LESS, $43.75;
3 (II) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN ITEM (IV) OF THIS PARAGRAPH,
4 FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MAXIMUM GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT OF MORE THAN 3,500
5 POUNDS BUT NOT MORE THAN 5,000 POUNDS, $48.75;
6 (III) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN ITEM (IV) OF THIS PARAGRAPH,
7 FOR A VEHICLE WITH A MAXIMUM GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT OF MORE THAN 5,000
8 POUNDS, $88.75; AND
9 (IV) FOR A VEHICLE, REGARDLESS OF THE VEHICLE’S MAXIMUM
10 GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT, FOR WHICH THE OWNER CERTIFIES ON THE
11 REGISTRATION APPLICATION THAT THE VEHICLE FOR WHICH THE APPLICATION IS
12 MADE WILL BE USED FOR CONSTRUCTION ACTIVITIES, $43.75.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
14 (a) When a bridge built over the Patapsco River to replace the collapsed Francis
15 Scott Key Bridge opens to general vehicular traffic, with no further action required by the
16 General Assembly, this Act shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
17 (b) The Maryland Transportation Authority shall notify the Department of
18 Legislative Services within 5 days of the Francis Scott Key Bridge reopening to general
19 vehicular traffic.
20 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2026.

